{"title":"Follower","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Follower","type":"markdown","data":"A **follower** is a monster that follows you from one [dungeon level](/wiki/Dungeon_level \"Dungeon level\") to another, if it happens to be next to when you when you change levels. These monsters follow you regardless of how you changed levels, whether a [staircase](/wiki/Staircase \"Staircase\"), [level teleport](/wiki/Level_teleport \"Level teleport\"), [trap](/wiki/Trap \"Trap\"), or any other means. [Elbereth](/wiki/Elbereth \"Elbereth\") will prevent this if the monster respects it.\n\nThe @ [Wizard of Yendor](/wiki/Wizard_of_Yendor \"Wizard of Yendor\") will never follow if he's carrying the real [Amulet of Yendor](/wiki/Amulet_of_Yendor \"Amulet of Yendor\"), and always otherwise. [Pets](/wiki/Pet \"Pet\") (unless they're eating) and hostile [shopkeepers](/wiki/Shopkeeper \"Shopkeeper\") will always follow. Other monsters will follow if they have the M2\\_STALK attribute defined, provided either they're not fleeing or you're carrying the real Amulet:\n\n- all [A](/wiki/Angelic_being \"Angelic being\") [T](/wiki/Troll_\\(monster_class\\) \"Troll (monster class)\") [V](/wiki/Vampire_\\(monster_class\\) \"Vampire (monster class)\") [W](/wiki/Wraith_\\(monster_class\\) \"Wraith (monster class)\") [i](/wiki/Imp_or_minor_demon \"Imp or minor demon\") [t](/wiki/Trapper_or_lurker_above \"Trapper or lurker above\") [&](/wiki/Major_demon \"Major demon\")\n- all [Z](/wiki/Zombie_\\(monster_class\\) \"Zombie (monster class)\") except Z [ghouls](/wiki/Ghoul \"Ghoul\") or Z [skeletons](/wiki/Skeleton \"Skeleton\")\n- all [quest nemeses](/wiki/Quest_nemeses \"Quest nemeses\")\n- all [mercenaries](/wiki/Mercenaries \"Mercenaries\") except @ [guards](/wiki/Guard \"Guard\")\n- g [gremlins](/wiki/Gremlin \"Gremlin\"), E [stalkers](/wiki/Stalker \"Stalker\"), : [salamanders](/wiki/Salamander \"Salamander\"),   [ghosts](/wiki/Ghost \"Ghost\"),   [shades](/wiki/Shade \"Shade\"), and @ [Croesus](/wiki/Croesus \"Croesus\")\n\nNote that except for shopkeepers, peaceful monsters will still follow you without any apparent motive. [Sessile](/wiki/Sessile \"Sessile\") pets will also follow, despite being unable to move otherwise.\n\nNot all [covetous](/wiki/Covetous \"Covetous\") monsters are followers. In particular, [liches](/wiki/Lich_\\(monster_class\\) \"Lich (monster class)\") won't follow you down stairs.\n\nSee [levl\\_follower](/wiki/Source:Mondata.c#levl_follower \"Source:Mondata.c\") in [mondata.c](/wiki/Source:Mondata.c \"Source:Mondata.c\").\n\n[![This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.4. Click here for more information.](/images/3/37/Nh364-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.4. Click here for more information.\")\n\n**This page may need to be updated for the [current version](/wiki/Current_version \"Current version\") of *NetHack*.**\n\nIt may contain text specific to [NetHack 3.6.4](/wiki/NetHack_3.6.4 \"NetHack 3.6.4\"). Information on this page may be out of date.\n\n**Editors:** After reviewing this page and making necessary edits, please change the {{nethack-364}} tag to the current version's tag or {{noversion}} as appropriate.\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Follower - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Follower\",\"wgTitle\":\"Follower\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":156568,\"wgRevisionId\":156568,\"wgArticleId\":11116,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Pages with unversioned Functi